Say Party Has Learnt Valuable Lessons From 2023 Poll ABUJA – The embattled National Chairman of the Labour Party, Julius Abure, has declared that the party has learnt its lessons from the February 25 presidential election, and that it will never again be found nabbing in future polls. Abure also disclosed that the party will stop at nothing to reclaim its mandate at the election petition tribunal. The LP national chairman made this known at a good governance summit for all 2023 Labour Party elected candidates organised by its Diaspora Chapters, in Abuja, on Thursday. Details later…